## Highest priority

### 1. Recipe library usefulness pass
Focus now:
- seed the recipe library with more real recipes already built together
- make the recipe DB feel useful instead of half-empty
- validate real-device browsing/filter flow now that the underlying structure is stronger
- improve category/filter behavior only where it still feels clunky
- identify any remaining friction in servings-based recipe logging
- expand and refine the **Ingredient Index** so the builder is genuinely useful in day-to-day use
- polish the **Recipe Builder** now that the foundation exists
- support:
  - ingredient rows
  - editable quantities/units
  - recipe total nutrition
  - servings
  - per-serving nutrition
  - save into the existing recipe system cleanly
- continue improving barcode-backed packaged food/product intake now that scanner + online lookup are live
- recipe image support remains optional and lower priority than Builder/Barcode usefulness

### 2. Supplement barcode/usefulness follow-through
Focus now:
- validate real-device supplement barcode flow end to end
- improve supplement create/edit UX when coming from barcode lookup
- confirm rescans reliably resolve to existing supplement records
- refine mapping only where lookup results are actually useful in practice

### 3. Backup / recovery confidence follow-through
Focus now:
- validate real restore behavior from the new master backup system on-device
- confirm nightly backup timing and retention behave correctly in real use
- confirm recovery is practical after reinstall/test churn
- only add custom backup location support if the default path becomes a real limitation

### 4. UX cleanup / settings hygiene follow-through
Focus now:
- keep settings organized as new pacing/health/supplement/backup/barcode options are added
- avoid turning Settings into a junk drawer
- continue visual cleanup to match intended dashboard style
- keep destructive actions clearly separated and understandable
- keep version/build info trustworthy
- only promote this work if real friction appears, not out of compulsive tinkering

### 5. Later reassessment
After more real-device usage, re-evaluate the order and decide what deserves to stay, split, or die.
